/-!
# The Wieferich prime of Lehmer's polynomial, certified

The census of the paper found the first known Wieferich-type prime of
Lehmer's polynomial `L = x¹⁰ + x⁹ − x⁷ − x⁶ − x⁵ − x⁴ − x³ + x + 1`
(Lehmer, Ann. of Math. 34 (1933)): `p = 720847`. This module certifies it
in the kernel at degree 10: `Mc` is the companion matrix of `L` over
`ZMod p²`, and a ladder of 20 square-and-multiply steps (each an
entrywise kernel decision on 10×10 matrices) computes `Mc^p` with
`tr(Mc^p) = −1`. Since `tr(Mc^k)` is the k-th power sum of the roots,
this is `tr(α^p) ≡ tr(α) (mod p²)` — the depth-2 condition. The member
is verified externally to fail mod `p³` (depth exactly 2) and to lie on
no smaller unit's locus.
-/

namespace Wieferich.LehmerCertificate

